1
00:00:00,080 --> 00:00:02,240
Wow, the bracelet shines
beautifully, brother.

2
00:00:02,360 --> 00:00:03,640
I love this gift.

3
00:00:04,000 --> 00:00:05,320
He bought the bracelet for Demet.

4
00:00:05,520 --> 00:00:06,920
He was only asking my opinion.

5
00:00:08,880 --> 00:00:09,880
She told the truth.

6
00:00:10,360 --> 00:00:11,760
The bracelet was for Demet.

7
00:00:12,200 --> 00:00:14,736
Even though you heard what Demet
said, what are you still saying?

8
00:00:14,760 --> 00:00:16,776
I am talking about the bracelet.
You do not even apologize.

9
00:00:16,800 --> 00:00:17,800
Sorry, what apology?

10
00:00:18,120 --> 00:00:19,639
Oh, pardon.

11
00:00:19,640 --> 00:00:20,640
You are right.

12
00:00:20,840 --> 00:00:22,880
Ateş Karahan never apologizes.

13
00:00:23,360 --> 00:00:24,360
I swear, Haydar,

14
00:00:24,640 --> 00:00:27,960
you are not a man who would care about
your daughter turning her back on you.

15
00:00:28,080 --> 00:00:29,920
Are you making fun of me, Nezir?

16
00:00:30,800 --> 00:00:33,480
Did you think you could put me in
the crosshairs and get rid of me?

17
00:00:33,960 --> 00:00:35,280
Is this what you are looking for?

18
00:00:36,040 --> 00:00:37,760
You have been very distracted lately.

19
00:00:37,800 --> 00:00:40,160
You are doing unexpected
things because of Mercan.

20
00:00:40,840 --> 00:00:42,320
I am a woman too, Ateş, I understand.

21
00:00:43,120 --> 00:00:46,120
The way a man looks at a
woman, the feelings he carries...

22
00:00:46,160 --> 00:00:47,160
Enough, mother Müzeyyen.

23
00:00:47,600 --> 00:00:49,000
He wants me to go to London.

24
00:00:49,440 --> 00:00:51,880
What’s his problem this
time, where did this come from?

25
00:00:52,160 --> 00:00:53,160
I don’t know.

26
00:00:54,160 --> 00:00:56,680
He said you’ll stay there
until the 187 days are over.

27
00:00:56,880 --> 00:00:57,880
You’re my daughter.

28
00:00:58,440 --> 00:00:59,680
Haydar Yıldırım’s daughter.

29
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:02,880
You’re not going anywhere just
because Mr. Ateş’s royal mood demands it.

30
00:01:03,440 --> 00:01:06,400
If I don’t go, he’ll
terminate the contract.

31
00:01:08,520 --> 00:01:09,800
We’ll lose everything.

32
00:01:10,360 --> 00:01:12,280
Ateş is sending her
because he doesn’t love her.

33
00:01:13,240 --> 00:01:15,160
And they won’t be glued
to each other anymore.

34
00:01:15,800 --> 00:01:17,440
That’s all I want, dear Aslı.

35
00:01:17,880 --> 00:01:20,040
Ateş isn’t sending Mercan
because he doesn’t love her.

36
00:01:20,440 --> 00:01:21,960
He’s sending her because he’s jealous.

37
00:01:22,080 --> 00:01:24,000
Jealous of you.

38
00:01:24,080 --> 00:01:25,120
Got it?

39
00:01:25,480 --> 00:01:26,680
Look, I’m honestly asking.

40
00:01:26,880 --> 00:01:28,400
Because I honestly don’t understand.

41
00:01:28,600 --> 00:01:30,360
Why all this anger, this hatred?

42
00:01:30,840 --> 00:01:32,800
Don’t tire yourself trying to understand.

43
00:01:32,960 --> 00:01:37,400
In fact, there’s no one in
this world I hate more than you.

44
00:01:38,120 --> 00:01:41,239
I won’t even get into a war of words
with you and sink to your level, alright?

45
00:01:41,240 --> 00:01:43,280
For you to get to my level...

46
00:01:43,480 --> 00:01:44,600
Aslı, enough.

47
00:01:46,360 --> 00:01:48,200
Don’t drag it out,
whatever it is, end it now.

48
00:01:49,480 --> 00:01:51,040
If you say don’t go.

49
00:01:51,200 --> 00:01:52,200
If you stay.

50
00:01:52,320 --> 00:01:53,880
Since you want it this much.

51
00:01:56,720 --> 00:01:57,920
I accept your offer.

52
00:01:59,320 --> 00:02:00,400
I’m going to London.

53
00:03:22,520 --> 00:03:25,080
We won't see each other
again until we get divorced.

54
00:03:25,160 --> 00:03:27,120
And after that, I’m gone for good, anyways.

55
00:03:29,120 --> 00:03:30,440
Fine by me.

56
00:03:35,480 --> 00:03:36,560
Same here.

57
00:03:38,680 --> 00:03:41,640
There’s nothing left for us
to do together in this life.

58
00:03:47,280 --> 00:03:48,760
Sounds wonderful.

59
00:03:53,720 --> 00:03:54,840
I think so too.

60
00:03:56,000 --> 00:03:57,280
You’ll relax.

61
00:03:59,120 --> 00:04:01,960
I already am.

62
00:04:04,080 --> 00:04:05,720
Oh, peace at last.

63
00:04:12,120 --> 00:04:13,120
Trust me, me too.

64
00:04:14,360 --> 00:04:16,800
Oh, such peace.

65
00:04:20,160 --> 00:04:22,440
We kept ending up in
the wrong places anyway.

66
00:04:25,960 --> 00:04:27,880
Now we’ll go to all the right ones.

67
00:04:30,960 --> 00:04:32,400
Exactly.

68
00:04:33,720 --> 00:04:36,480
Once you’re gone, I’ll
be rid of my biggest problem.

69
00:04:42,240 --> 00:04:43,400
What a coincidence.

70
00:04:44,480 --> 00:04:46,360
Turns out we feel the same.

71
00:04:51,880 --> 00:04:54,760
Look at that. We finally
agree on something.

72
00:04:56,280 --> 00:04:57,280
Right?

73
00:04:58,000 --> 00:04:59,560
At least we managed that.

74
00:05:00,360 --> 00:05:01,560
Lucky us.

75
00:05:03,960 --> 00:05:05,160
Sure.

76
00:05:26,240 --> 00:05:27,640
I wish you'd tell me to stay.

77
00:05:50,440 --> 00:05:51,840
I wish you’d not go.

78
00:05:53,400 --> 00:05:54,680
I don't want you to leave.

79
00:06:35,520 --> 00:06:36,960
Çiçek, what’s wrong?

80
00:06:40,160 --> 00:06:41,360
Did I do something wrong?

81
00:06:43,400 --> 00:06:45,760
Did I hurt your feelings without realizing?

82
00:06:47,320 --> 00:06:49,040
Nothing’s wrong.

83
00:06:52,360 --> 00:06:55,560
Maybe that’s the problem.

84
00:06:58,200 --> 00:07:00,800
I swear, I don’t understand
what you’re trying to say.

85
00:07:01,040 --> 00:07:02,480
Just tell me straight, Çiçek.

86
00:07:02,720 --> 00:07:04,520
Oh!

87
00:07:12,120 --> 00:07:14,360
Let me check the cars.

88
00:07:16,280 --> 00:07:18,200
Mom, would you like some tea?

89
00:07:18,680 --> 00:07:19,680
No, dear.

90
00:07:22,160 --> 00:07:23,200
Oh - oh.

91
00:07:23,840 --> 00:07:25,400
What’s wrong?

92
00:07:27,520 --> 00:07:28,760
It’s Mercan…

93
00:07:29,240 --> 00:07:30,320
What about her?

94
00:07:31,800 --> 00:07:35,280
They’re practically sending the girl
away like an exile because of the Karahans.

95
00:07:36,640 --> 00:07:38,840
What? Seriously?

96
00:07:42,280 --> 00:07:45,120
What’s she supposed to do
all by herself over there?

97
00:07:46,240 --> 00:07:48,120
That’s awful… I'm sorry for her.

98
00:07:48,760 --> 00:07:50,040
Me too, dear.

99
00:07:50,880 --> 00:07:52,560
I raised that child.

100
00:07:52,960 --> 00:07:54,800
Among them, she's the kindest

101
00:07:54,880 --> 00:07:57,480
and the sweetest.

102
00:07:57,840 --> 00:08:00,800
Nothing like her family.

103
00:08:00,880 --> 00:08:05,280
You’d never guess she
came from that bloodline.

104
00:08:05,360 --> 00:08:06,440
She’s different.

105
00:08:06,840 --> 00:08:08,480
She really is.

106
00:08:09,040 --> 00:08:12,520
Always respectful, always loving.

107
00:08:13,560 --> 00:08:16,160
Never hurts anyone.

108
00:08:17,360 --> 00:08:18,880
Well dear,

109
00:08:18,960 --> 00:08:20,440
In a place run by the wicked,

110
00:08:20,640 --> 00:08:22,320
a good person sticks out like a thorn.

111
00:08:22,960 --> 00:08:24,520
The wicked tolerate each other

112
00:08:24,720 --> 00:08:26,360
but they can’t stomach the good.

113
00:08:26,800 --> 00:08:30,400
Mercan’s a rose trying to grow in a swamp.

114
00:08:30,720 --> 00:08:33,000
People admire her from afar,

115
00:08:33,320 --> 00:08:35,280
but only she knows what she endures.

116
00:08:37,320 --> 00:08:38,720
Oh, my...

117
00:08:38,880 --> 00:08:41,960
They make the mess, she pays the price.

118
00:08:43,240 --> 00:08:46,000
Oh, my kind mama…

119
00:08:46,120 --> 00:08:47,840
My soft hearted mama…

120
00:08:49,000 --> 00:08:51,320
I’m so lucky you’re mine.

121
00:09:44,560 --> 00:09:46,320
He’s sending me away from my home…

122
00:09:53,680 --> 00:09:55,560
From the place I lived, loved, belonged.

123
00:09:55,960 --> 00:09:58,720
Just ripping me out.

124
00:10:00,840 --> 00:10:03,160
We kept ending up in
the wrong places anyway.

125
00:10:05,000 --> 00:10:07,640
Once you’re gone, I’ll
be rid of my biggest problem.

126
00:10:14,800 --> 00:10:16,360
I’m the one escaping… not him.

127
00:11:00,000 --> 00:11:01,800
’Cause I know you won’t listen to me.

128
00:11:01,880 --> 00:11:03,040
I'm talking in vain.

129
00:11:03,120 --> 00:11:04,920
We’re stuck in this vicious cycle.

130
00:11:05,000 --> 00:11:06,720
The same things. Over and over again.

131
00:11:06,800 --> 00:11:08,680
I'm sick of this. Okay? I'm sick of this.

132
00:11:35,640 --> 00:11:37,040
I’m getting rid of all of you.

133
00:11:37,840 --> 00:11:40,400
You, Müzeyyen, Aslı…

134
00:11:42,040 --> 00:11:44,480
The family I thought I knew, but never did.

135
00:12:09,480 --> 00:12:11,920
Instead of living inside a crowded lie,

136
00:12:13,280 --> 00:12:16,000
maybe it’s better to be exiled on my own.

137
00:12:19,160 --> 00:12:21,040
But why does it hurt this much?

138
00:13:10,640 --> 00:13:12,040
Are you alright?

139
00:13:12,880 --> 00:13:14,800
Why wouldn’t I be?

140
00:13:15,080 --> 00:13:16,920
I don’t know. You didn’t look okay.

141
00:13:17,120 --> 00:13:18,520
That’s why I asked.

142
00:13:20,280 --> 00:13:21,840
You must’ve imagined it.

143
00:13:23,400 --> 00:13:25,960
Like I said, I felt relieved
once I made my decision.

144
00:13:27,840 --> 00:13:29,000
Anyways,

145
00:13:29,120 --> 00:13:30,240
I should go.

146
00:13:30,320 --> 00:13:31,720
I have a lot to do.

147
00:13:33,480 --> 00:13:34,840
I need to make a list

148
00:13:36,200 --> 00:13:38,080
so I don’t forget anything.

149
00:13:39,040 --> 00:13:41,200
Nothing of mine should stay here.

150
00:13:45,360 --> 00:13:49,240
You can’t take the you I
carry in my heart anywhere.

151
00:14:02,120 --> 00:14:03,360
Good then.

152
00:14:03,480 --> 00:14:04,840
She’s finally leaving.

153
00:14:05,560 --> 00:14:08,600
For a moment I thought she’d stay.

154
00:14:10,360 --> 00:14:13,120
At least she won’t be
around for a long time.

155
00:14:13,960 --> 00:14:15,200
And once the divorce is done

156
00:14:15,280 --> 00:14:16,920
she'll be out of our lives completely.

157
00:14:19,760 --> 00:14:21,600
Gone forever.

158
00:14:29,800 --> 00:14:30,840
Come in, son.

159
00:14:30,960 --> 00:14:32,920
We were just talking about Mercan leaving.

160
00:14:34,320 --> 00:14:36,320
Things will be so much better.

161
00:14:36,560 --> 00:14:38,680
Together, just like always.

162
00:14:39,800 --> 00:14:41,840
We should’ve crushed
that little snake earlier.

163
00:14:41,920 --> 00:14:43,040
But anyway.

164
00:14:43,120 --> 00:14:44,760
Let's manage the ones here for now.

165
00:14:44,920 --> 00:14:46,600
We’ll deal with that later.

166
00:14:48,600 --> 00:14:50,840
The real guilty ones are Haydar and Nermin.

167
00:14:52,240 --> 00:14:53,680
Not Mercan.

168
00:14:57,640 --> 00:14:59,600
Stop aiming your anger at the wrong person.

169
00:15:00,600 --> 00:15:02,040
Wrong?

170
00:15:02,400 --> 00:15:04,160
She’s done plenty.

171
00:15:05,200 --> 00:15:07,200
You know, she protected her brother.

172
00:15:10,720 --> 00:15:12,680
Now she protects her father.

173
00:15:13,400 --> 00:15:15,240
She’s not innocent, Ateş.

174
00:15:16,200 --> 00:15:17,760
This punishment is enough.

175
00:15:18,960 --> 00:15:20,280
No need for more.

176
00:15:20,800 --> 00:15:23,800
Why be soft with her?

177
00:15:25,200 --> 00:15:26,520
She’s a Yıldırım too.

178
00:15:29,720 --> 00:15:32,120
So what? Should I
torture an innocent person

179
00:15:32,760 --> 00:15:34,920
just because of her bloodline?

180
00:15:38,400 --> 00:15:41,600
If I locked her in a cellar,

181
00:15:42,680 --> 00:15:44,760
you’d ask why I gave her bread.

182
00:15:47,800 --> 00:15:49,680
If I took the bread, but give her water,

183
00:15:50,080 --> 00:15:51,920
you’d ask why I gave her water.

184
00:15:53,440 --> 00:15:54,600
What do you want?

185
00:15:55,120 --> 00:15:56,880
What will finally satisfy you?

186
00:15:59,960 --> 00:16:03,600
I won’t be satisfied until
I take revenge on that family.

187
00:16:06,880 --> 00:16:09,240
They’re all the same to me.

188
00:16:13,720 --> 00:16:15,520
You may see her differently

189
00:16:15,880 --> 00:16:17,640
but to me there’s no difference.

190
00:16:18,440 --> 00:16:19,480
In all this filth,

191
00:16:19,560 --> 00:16:21,040
who’s managed to stay clean anyway?

192
00:16:21,120 --> 00:16:22,280
Why should she?

193
00:16:27,080 --> 00:16:29,720
She should share her family’s fate.

194
00:16:29,880 --> 00:16:31,080
If it’s ruin, it’s ruin.

195
00:16:31,520 --> 00:16:32,840
If it’s death, it’s death.

196
00:16:41,080 --> 00:16:43,520
Ladies… breathe.

197
00:16:47,000 --> 00:16:49,360
We came here to punish the guilty,

198
00:16:50,880 --> 00:16:53,160
not torture the innocent.

199
00:16:59,480 --> 00:17:00,840
Don’t forget that.

200
00:17:04,960 --> 00:17:06,680
If you fight monsters without caution,

201
00:17:07,400 --> 00:17:09,560
you become one.

202
00:17:10,880 --> 00:17:12,160
I’m not a monster.

203
00:17:12,640 --> 00:17:15,040
Don’t judge me for refusing to become one.

204
00:17:18,560 --> 00:17:21,560
I want justice for the past.

205
00:17:22,920 --> 00:17:24,520
My intentions

206
00:17:24,800 --> 00:17:26,720
and my reckoning go no further than that.

207
00:18:04,880 --> 00:18:06,520
It’s time.

208
00:18:17,160 --> 00:18:19,720
- Çiçek?
- What are you doing tonight? Got plans?

209
00:18:20,240 --> 00:18:21,800
-Tonight? -Yeah.

210
00:18:21,880 --> 00:18:24,640
Tonight? Uh… yeah. I’ve got… something.

211
00:18:25,760 --> 00:18:27,120
What "something"?

212
00:18:28,080 --> 00:18:30,640
You know, Çiçek … stuff. Work stuff.

213
00:18:31,320 --> 00:18:32,600
No, I don’t know.

214
00:18:32,680 --> 00:18:33,920
What work?

215
00:18:34,360 --> 00:18:35,680
Uh... no.

216
00:18:36,120 --> 00:18:37,440
Just regular work.

217
00:18:37,520 --> 00:18:38,760
Okay but what is it?

218
00:18:38,840 --> 00:18:41,360
-Uh, this... behind... -Malik.

219
00:18:43,720 --> 00:18:45,960
Help me move the water pump.

220
00:18:46,040 --> 00:18:47,560
Coming, bro!

221
00:18:50,760 --> 00:18:52,640
Isn't he going to propose to me?

222
00:19:18,520 --> 00:19:21,320
We’re not seeing each other
again until the divorce is final.

223
00:19:22,800 --> 00:19:25,080
And after that, I’m gone for good, anyways.

224
00:19:26,120 --> 00:19:29,320
There’s nothing left for us
to do together in this life.

225
00:20:06,640 --> 00:20:08,000
Listen, Ateş.

226
00:20:09,240 --> 00:20:10,840
If you want, we can get out of here.

227
00:20:10,920 --> 00:20:12,960
Clear our heads a little.

228
00:20:13,640 --> 00:20:16,200
The last thing I need right
now is to clear my head.

229
00:20:17,240 --> 00:20:18,640
On the contrary, I need to focus.

230
00:20:19,640 --> 00:20:21,560
Then do what you want.

231
00:20:23,320 --> 00:20:25,920
Just make sure you’re focusing
on the right thing, Ateş.

232
00:20:29,440 --> 00:20:31,960
Sometimes one word is
enough to fix everything.

233
00:20:37,360 --> 00:20:40,320
Some words are heavier
than you think, Cemal.

234
00:20:44,720 --> 00:20:46,640
They sound easy in your mind…

235
00:20:48,320 --> 00:20:50,280
but when you try to say them,

236
00:20:52,120 --> 00:20:53,760
they just won’t come out.

237
00:20:56,200 --> 00:20:57,600
I know it, Ateş.

238
00:20:58,040 --> 00:20:59,640
I know.

239
00:21:03,880 --> 00:21:05,280
Still… try.

240
00:21:05,440 --> 00:21:06,920
What do you have to lose?

241
00:21:35,720 --> 00:21:38,200
Hey, sweetheart! How are you?

242
00:21:39,120 --> 00:21:40,440
I’m fine. Thanks.

243
00:21:41,680 --> 00:21:44,000
We haven’t spoken in so long, Mercan.

244
00:21:44,560 --> 00:21:47,080
I have so much to tell you.

245
00:21:49,760 --> 00:21:51,680
I’m listening.

246
00:21:53,640 --> 00:21:55,080
You know Burak?

247
00:21:55,960 --> 00:21:58,120
He’s nothing like he looks.

248
00:21:59,120 --> 00:22:01,920
You’d think he’s clumsy...

249
00:22:03,800 --> 00:22:04,840
and goofy,

250
00:22:04,920 --> 00:22:07,000
but once you get to know
him he’s actually really…

251
00:22:08,160 --> 00:22:09,560
Really…?

252
00:22:10,360 --> 00:22:12,360
Really polite. And fun.

253
00:22:13,720 --> 00:22:15,400
We had such a great time at the concert.

254
00:22:17,800 --> 00:22:21,080
No one’s made me feel
this good in a long time.

255
00:22:22,600 --> 00:22:24,240
Sometimes the person you need

256
00:22:24,320 --> 00:22:26,360
is the one you never expected.

257
00:22:37,840 --> 00:22:40,000
So… why did you call everyone together?

258
00:22:43,800 --> 00:22:45,240
I have news.

259
00:22:46,760 --> 00:22:48,520
And it’s time.

260
00:22:49,200 --> 00:22:50,440
Come on.

261
00:23:00,880 --> 00:23:02,320
I called you all here

262
00:23:02,560 --> 00:23:04,840
to share some news… and to say goodbye.

263
00:23:15,280 --> 00:23:16,840
It was sudden for me too.

264
00:23:21,120 --> 00:23:23,160
I’m going abroad for a few months.

265
00:23:26,840 --> 00:23:28,240
But we’ll stay in touch.

266
00:23:28,400 --> 00:23:30,720
If you need anything, call me.

267
00:23:35,640 --> 00:23:39,360
I’ll help however I can from there.

268
00:23:50,000 --> 00:23:51,840
It’s a short goodbye…

269
00:23:53,280 --> 00:23:55,280
but I’ll miss this place and all of you.

270
00:24:05,560 --> 00:24:07,240
We’ll miss you so much, Mrs. Mercan.

271
00:24:12,080 --> 00:24:13,320
Mercan...

272
00:24:13,400 --> 00:24:17,040
Where did this come from all of a sudden?

273
00:24:28,560 --> 00:24:30,000
It had to happen.

274
00:24:30,560 --> 00:24:32,840
-I have to go. -But why?

275
00:24:44,000 --> 00:24:46,080
Video call me day or night. Will you?

276
00:24:46,360 --> 00:24:48,360
In order to talk to
me about Burak or else.

277
00:24:54,120 --> 00:24:55,600
Yaşar...

278
00:24:56,560 --> 00:24:59,160
by the time I’m back, you’d
have completed your trip to India.

279
00:24:59,280 --> 00:25:00,560
-Right? -India?

280
00:25:00,960 --> 00:25:03,840
I will, Mercan Hanım. For you.

281
00:25:04,000 --> 00:25:06,200
I'll send you videos from the yoga retreat.

282
00:25:07,000 --> 00:25:08,440
Alright.

283
00:25:15,400 --> 00:25:18,760
Sometimes sudden changes…

284
00:25:19,760 --> 00:25:22,440
even short separations…

285
00:25:22,680 --> 00:25:25,640
remind you how precious every moment is.

286
00:25:26,720 --> 00:25:28,800
Don’t give up on the things you love.

287
00:25:31,200 --> 00:25:32,720
Promise me

288
00:25:33,800 --> 00:25:36,520
you won’t waste your
days on anger or grudges.

289
00:25:37,080 --> 00:25:39,120
Focus on being happy.

290
00:25:41,200 --> 00:25:43,280
How am I supposed to endure your absence?

291
00:25:46,440 --> 00:25:50,160
And take really good care of yourselves.

292
00:26:10,800 --> 00:26:12,560
You're ones I trust most here.

293
00:26:13,640 --> 00:26:15,360
Keep me updated, okay?

294
00:26:17,280 --> 00:26:19,480
Mrs. Mercan I'll call you frequently.

295
00:26:20,200 --> 00:26:22,080
All the time.

296
00:26:25,040 --> 00:26:26,280
Don’t worry, honey.

297
00:26:26,480 --> 00:26:28,760
We’ll keep you in the loop.

298
00:28:05,520 --> 00:28:07,560
We went through so much together.

299
00:28:51,200 --> 00:28:52,760
Come in.

300
00:29:10,040 --> 00:29:12,400
I wanted to talk about
the hospital project.

301
00:29:13,400 --> 00:29:16,200
You’ll handle it while I’m abroad, right?

302
00:29:17,960 --> 00:29:19,560
Is that what you came to say?

303
00:29:22,120 --> 00:29:23,920
Were you expecting something else?

304
00:29:25,480 --> 00:29:26,840
What would I expect?

305
00:29:28,360 --> 00:29:29,760
If we’re talking business…

306
00:29:30,800 --> 00:29:32,120
Then be professional.

307
00:29:33,360 --> 00:29:34,760
Finish what you started.

308
00:29:36,280 --> 00:29:38,520
If seeing me didn’t get
under your skin this much,

309
00:29:38,600 --> 00:29:40,400
if you could tolerate me for just a while…

310
00:29:40,480 --> 00:29:41,720
I’d finish it.

311
00:29:44,320 --> 00:29:45,600
If you want to, you can.

312
00:29:46,920 --> 00:29:48,680
How am I supposed to do that from abroad?

313
00:29:50,240 --> 00:29:51,520
That’s your problem.

314
00:29:54,280 --> 00:29:56,280
Everything is always my problem, isn’t it?

315
00:29:57,600 --> 00:29:59,240
You’re so confident.

316
00:30:00,880 --> 00:30:02,280
Why does this create a problem?

317
00:30:02,360 --> 00:30:04,320
I’m not the one creating
the problem. You are.

318
00:30:06,120 --> 00:30:07,480
Let’s say I am.

319
00:30:08,520 --> 00:30:09,880
And it is your job to fix it.

320
00:30:12,240 --> 00:30:14,000
Are you trying to push me?

321
00:30:14,760 --> 00:30:16,080
Can’t handle pressure?

322
00:30:18,160 --> 00:30:19,640
I won't die like this Karahan.

323
00:30:20,840 --> 00:30:23,040
I survived living in that mansion with you.

324
00:30:24,040 --> 00:30:25,800
I can handle this with my eyes closed.

325
00:30:28,280 --> 00:30:29,520
Fine.

326
00:30:31,520 --> 00:30:33,080
Then stand by your words.

327
00:30:42,920 --> 00:30:44,040
Don’t worry.

328
00:30:44,600 --> 00:30:46,680
I always do.

329
00:30:47,440 --> 00:30:48,960
Maybe remind yourself of that.

330
00:30:50,400 --> 00:30:53,160
If you delay the project
and the company takes a hit,

331
00:30:56,280 --> 00:30:58,240
the consequences will be serious.

332
00:30:58,320 --> 00:30:59,400
For your info.

333
00:31:06,720 --> 00:31:09,680
If you’re going to punish
me unfairly like you do now,

334
00:31:10,120 --> 00:31:11,800
it won’t matter what I do.

335
00:31:41,640 --> 00:31:43,960
NERMİN: To be seen as a leader,

336
00:31:44,040 --> 00:31:45,760
you must surprise people…

337
00:31:51,000 --> 00:31:55,160
Act beyond their expectations.

338
00:32:02,840 --> 00:32:04,080
That’s me.

339
00:32:09,840 --> 00:32:12,680
I won’t let you take that
foundation chair, Müzeyyen.

340
00:32:26,160 --> 00:32:27,400
Where’s my jacket?

341
00:32:35,720 --> 00:32:37,040
On the back of the chair.

342
00:32:42,200 --> 00:32:43,520
What are you doing?

343
00:32:45,400 --> 00:32:47,360
I'm running for the foundation presidency.

344
00:32:48,000 --> 00:32:49,440
I’m preparing my campaign for it.

345
00:32:49,840 --> 00:32:52,080
Your daughter’s going to
London, everything’s a mess,

346
00:32:52,160 --> 00:32:53,640
and this is what you’re focused on?

347
00:32:53,720 --> 00:32:55,640
This country is
overflowing with presidents.

348
00:32:55,720 --> 00:32:57,160
You were the only one missing.

349
00:32:59,440 --> 00:33:02,040
You're talking as if
you didn't agree to it.

350
00:33:02,960 --> 00:33:05,960
Besides, worry about us.

351
00:33:07,880 --> 00:33:09,880
Soon it’ll just be the two of us left here.

352
00:33:11,000 --> 00:33:12,680
True… but we’re stronger now.

353
00:33:13,320 --> 00:33:15,040
I bought shares from Nezir’s company.

354
00:33:15,680 --> 00:33:18,760
More money means more power.

355
00:33:20,600 --> 00:33:23,880
Exactly. You're absolutely right.

356
00:33:25,000 --> 00:33:26,400
If you have money, you exist.

357
00:33:27,160 --> 00:33:30,280
If you don’t, you’re nothing.

358
00:33:31,320 --> 00:33:33,120
Why do the Karahans get to call the shots?

359
00:33:33,800 --> 00:33:35,360
Because they have money, that’s why.

360
00:33:37,680 --> 00:33:39,360
Make those Karahans

361
00:33:39,600 --> 00:33:41,880
kneel in front of me in the garden

362
00:33:42,600 --> 00:33:44,480
and I won’t ask for anything else.

363
00:33:45,600 --> 00:33:47,520
Especially Müzeyyen.

364
00:33:49,280 --> 00:33:53,160
We didn’t get here by playing safe, Nermin.

365
00:33:54,120 --> 00:33:55,400
Trust your husband.

366
00:33:56,000 --> 00:33:57,920
Just… don’t draw attention for a while.

367
00:33:58,240 --> 00:33:59,640
That's all.

368
00:34:01,040 --> 00:34:02,240
See you later.

369
00:34:14,200 --> 00:34:17,160
Emotions are the first
doorway to our decisions.

370
00:34:17,560 --> 00:34:19,120
Huh.

371
00:34:27,960 --> 00:34:29,320
Mercan.

372
00:34:33,000 --> 00:34:34,720
You know I’m always here for you.

373
00:34:36,400 --> 00:34:38,560
Doesn’t matter whether
you’re here or in London.

374
00:34:39,600 --> 00:34:40,840
Just don’t worry.

375
00:34:44,920 --> 00:34:48,080
I’ll get rid of those
Karahans and bring you back.

376
00:34:50,640 --> 00:34:53,320
I swear, I’m fired up.

377
00:34:54,320 --> 00:34:55,800
Everything will be better.

378
00:34:57,480 --> 00:34:58,960
Better than before.

379
00:35:05,480 --> 00:35:07,920
Like I said, I’m here for anything.

380
00:35:08,160 --> 00:35:10,480
Just call when you need me.

381
00:35:19,240 --> 00:35:21,240
Thank you for your friendship, Nezir.

382
00:35:23,080 --> 00:35:25,160
But I can take care of myself.

383
00:35:31,480 --> 00:35:33,760
If you really want to do something for me…

384
00:35:34,240 --> 00:35:35,760
take care of Demet.

385
00:37:54,000 --> 00:37:55,480
Oh, God.

386
00:38:04,200 --> 00:38:05,520
Take a good look around.

387
00:38:05,880 --> 00:38:08,120
Remember everything and everybody.

388
00:38:09,320 --> 00:38:11,880
When you come back, you
might not find it the same.

389
00:38:16,320 --> 00:38:17,320
As they say...

390
00:38:17,760 --> 00:38:19,640
Leaving is easy,
returning is another story.

391
00:38:24,280 --> 00:38:26,840
You won’t find what you
left behind when you return.

392
00:38:32,240 --> 00:38:33,680
Mrs. Müzeyyen!

393
00:38:40,320 --> 00:38:41,600
Yes, Mrs. Müzeyyen.

394
00:38:42,800 --> 00:38:44,280
I will return.

395
00:38:46,880 --> 00:38:49,760
And I hope I don’t
find this place the same.

396
00:38:51,400 --> 00:38:53,120
And I hope I never see you again.

397
00:39:04,720 --> 00:39:05,880
Absolutely, dear.

398
00:39:06,280 --> 00:39:07,640
That’s exactly how it’ll be.

399
00:39:08,520 --> 00:39:10,000
Watch your tone.

400
00:39:10,720 --> 00:39:12,720
You don’t talk to my mother like that.

401
00:39:17,240 --> 00:39:19,040
Everyone be quiet, already!

402
00:39:27,480 --> 00:39:30,440
Well… what’s meant to
happen will happen, Mrs. bride.

403
00:39:34,920 --> 00:39:36,440
We’ll see.

404
00:39:38,000 --> 00:39:39,680
Enough!

405
00:40:26,960 --> 00:40:29,680
Hello, ma’am. Good evening.

406
00:40:29,960 --> 00:40:31,200
It’s me again.

407
00:40:32,040 --> 00:40:33,600
Uh, I made the arrangements.

408
00:40:34,120 --> 00:40:37,320
If you'd like, come to the
location I'll send you so we can talk.

409
00:40:38,920 --> 00:40:41,040
Okay. Yes, of course.

410
00:40:41,160 --> 00:40:42,480
We'll talk the details tomorrow.

411
00:40:43,080 --> 00:40:44,760
See you tomorrow.

412
00:40:46,960 --> 00:40:48,200
Çiçek?

413
00:40:48,320 --> 00:40:49,480
Who were you talking to?

414
00:40:49,560 --> 00:40:51,320
All that “of course, of course, okay”…?

415
00:40:51,520 --> 00:40:52,960
Who was I talking to?

416
00:40:53,040 --> 00:40:54,800
I asked who you were talking to.

417
00:40:55,440 --> 00:40:57,160
Who would I be talking to, Çiçek?

418
00:40:57,520 --> 00:40:59,320
Why are you interrogating me?

419
00:41:00,280 --> 00:41:01,360
Because I want to.

420
00:41:01,440 --> 00:41:03,400
Why wouldn't I?

421
00:41:05,560 --> 00:41:07,200
I heard you talking to a woman.

422
00:41:07,280 --> 00:41:09,320
I was talking to a woman? What woman?

423
00:41:09,440 --> 00:41:12,640
What are you implying? Tell me directly.

424
00:41:14,200 --> 00:41:15,520
Nothing.

425
00:41:15,800 --> 00:41:19,200
Good.

426
00:41:19,280 --> 00:41:21,280
Good night, then.

427
00:41:21,520 --> 00:41:22,920
Good night.

428
00:41:24,040 --> 00:41:25,480
Go, of course go!

429
00:41:26,760 --> 00:41:28,960
Men are cowards by nature!

430
00:41:33,640 --> 00:41:35,640
He definitely bought
that ring for someone else.

431
00:41:37,680 --> 00:41:39,200
He’s cheating on me.

432
00:41:41,800 --> 00:41:43,520
This is it, Çiçek…

433
00:41:43,600 --> 00:41:45,000
Ugh, it's over.

434
00:41:45,280 --> 00:41:46,600
We're done.

435
00:41:47,200 --> 00:41:48,760
When did he even have the time?

436
00:41:49,240 --> 00:41:51,080
How come I didn't notice it?

437
00:41:51,760 --> 00:41:54,600
Ugh, men.

438
00:41:55,160 --> 00:41:56,640
Just do it.

439
00:41:58,200 --> 00:42:01,400
How come I didn't notice it, you
being right in front of my eyes?

440
00:42:02,600 --> 00:42:04,160
Hm.

441
00:42:04,800 --> 00:42:06,720
But I’m Çiçek!

442
00:42:06,800 --> 00:42:09,720
I’ll teach you a lesson.

443
00:42:10,120 --> 00:42:11,600
You runaway groom.

444
00:44:06,040 --> 00:44:07,680
What am I even preparing for?

445
00:44:09,320 --> 00:44:11,040
What am I taking with me?

446
00:44:16,360 --> 00:44:18,960
Nothing but disappointment…

447
00:44:24,520 --> 00:44:25,960
He didn’t even listen.

448
00:44:27,480 --> 00:44:28,800
He just said "go."

449
00:44:33,520 --> 00:44:34,880
Tiny...

450
00:44:36,280 --> 00:44:38,280
just one tiny word…

451
00:44:40,600 --> 00:44:42,440
and it ends everything.

452
00:44:43,920 --> 00:44:45,400
Everything.

453
00:45:32,360 --> 00:45:35,440
Obviously, you’re Infected with
the disease called Mercan, Ateş.

454
00:45:36,200 --> 00:45:37,840
But I’m both your doctor

455
00:45:38,200 --> 00:45:39,720
and your medicine.

456
00:45:39,920 --> 00:45:41,440
I will cure you.

457
00:45:41,760 --> 00:45:43,920
I’ll cut out the rot.

458
00:45:45,560 --> 00:45:48,200
I'll kill that microbe

459
00:45:50,720 --> 00:45:52,240
before it takes you from me.

460
00:46:49,000 --> 00:46:51,320
If you’re changing, I can leave.

461
00:46:52,040 --> 00:46:53,880
I’ll change outside.

462
00:46:59,000 --> 00:47:00,560
Good night.

463
00:47:10,640 --> 00:47:12,000
Sleep…

464
00:47:12,880 --> 00:47:14,160
There’s no sleep.

465
00:47:14,640 --> 00:47:16,200
No peace.

466
00:47:16,400 --> 00:47:18,080
Nothing.

467
00:47:51,920 --> 00:47:53,400
He went into her room again.

468
00:47:54,680 --> 00:47:56,520
He can’t live without her, apparently.

469
00:47:57,880 --> 00:48:00,120
What does he see in Mercan?

470
00:48:01,160 --> 00:48:03,320
What does she have that I don’t?

471
00:48:04,480 --> 00:48:06,240
Why can’t he let her go?

472
00:48:10,920 --> 00:48:12,640
Ateş,

473
00:48:15,720 --> 00:48:17,320
if you can’t give her up…

474
00:48:18,000 --> 00:48:19,480
I’ll help you.

475
00:48:21,720 --> 00:48:23,400
I’ll do this for both of us.

476
00:48:52,520 --> 00:48:53,920
My dear daughter.

477
00:48:55,880 --> 00:48:57,320
Sweetheart.

478
00:49:09,240 --> 00:49:11,680
Ateş and Cemal are like sons to me…

479
00:49:12,480 --> 00:49:14,160
But you’re my daughter.

480
00:49:15,160 --> 00:49:17,760
The whole world on one
side, you on the other.

481
00:49:20,280 --> 00:49:22,960
I can’t stand to see you suffer,

482
00:49:24,560 --> 00:49:26,080
and I won’t let you, either.

483
00:49:28,160 --> 00:49:29,800
But be patient, my girl.

484
00:49:30,960 --> 00:49:33,160
That fire in you is going
to get you into trouble.

485
00:49:36,640 --> 00:49:37,920
You have to know when to burn…

486
00:49:38,000 --> 00:49:39,400
and when to cool.

487
00:50:08,040 --> 00:50:09,520
For our revenge…

488
00:50:12,040 --> 00:50:13,960
for Ateş to come to his senses…

489
00:50:14,920 --> 00:50:17,280
Mercan has to go.

490
00:50:20,840 --> 00:50:22,920
If I’m the only one who sees that,

491
00:50:24,560 --> 00:50:26,320
then it’s my job to do it.

492
00:50:30,000 --> 00:50:31,560
This ends tomorrow.

493
00:50:34,680 --> 00:50:36,080
Tomorrow,

494
00:50:37,240 --> 00:50:39,960
Mercan disappears forever.

495
00:50:55,640 --> 00:50:58,160
Did you do what I asked?

496
00:51:01,800 --> 00:51:03,440
As I said, the rest of the money comes

497
00:51:03,520 --> 00:51:05,000
when it’s done.

498
00:51:07,080 --> 00:51:08,400
Make sure it’s clean.

499
00:51:11,960 --> 00:51:13,200
Okay.

500
00:51:14,280 --> 00:51:16,120
No traces.

501
00:51:20,120 --> 00:51:21,360
Alright.

502
00:52:01,280 --> 00:52:02,760
I left my phone here…

503
00:52:14,680 --> 00:52:16,800
If you want… you can stay here tonight.

504
00:52:31,760 --> 00:52:33,760
I’m leaving tomorrow anyway.

505
00:52:39,040 --> 00:52:40,800
This room will be yours again.

506
00:52:41,800 --> 00:52:43,720
I just… thought you’d sleep better here.

507
00:52:54,800 --> 00:52:56,000
Yes,

508
00:52:56,560 --> 00:52:57,720
You’re right.

509
00:53:10,840 --> 00:53:13,040
Nights smell different here.

510
00:53:13,120 --> 00:53:15,120
Did you ever notice?

511
00:53:24,720 --> 00:53:26,000
I did.

512
00:53:32,720 --> 00:53:34,720
That’s why I love the night.

513
00:53:36,240 --> 00:53:38,320
I could sit here and
look at it till morning.

514
00:54:01,160 --> 00:54:02,760
Listen...

515
00:54:03,360 --> 00:54:05,200
It’s so quiet… so peaceful.

516
00:54:13,240 --> 00:54:14,600
Yes.

517
00:54:17,800 --> 00:54:19,320
Like nothing painful

518
00:54:20,120 --> 00:54:21,960
ever happened.

519
00:54:24,080 --> 00:54:26,000
And yet… so much did.

520
00:54:37,200 --> 00:54:39,280
I’ll miss this place.

521
00:54:43,280 --> 00:54:44,560
I’ll miss it a lot.

522
00:55:01,200 --> 00:55:02,560
But I’ll get over it.

523
00:55:04,160 --> 00:55:05,960
London’s not bad.

524
00:55:06,800 --> 00:55:08,280
I like it there too.

525
00:55:11,120 --> 00:55:12,600
Right.

526
00:55:17,160 --> 00:55:18,800
Not as good as here…

527
00:55:21,080 --> 00:55:22,560
but not bad.

528
00:55:29,120 --> 00:55:30,520
I should sleep.

529
00:55:31,640 --> 00:55:33,360
Travel day tomorrow.

530
00:55:34,160 --> 00:55:35,600
I need to wake up early.

531
00:55:45,560 --> 00:55:46,680
Good night, then.

532
00:55:53,800 --> 00:55:55,120
Good night.

533
00:56:35,640 --> 00:56:37,520
Want the light off or on?

534
00:56:39,520 --> 00:56:40,960
Whatever you want.

535
00:56:47,720 --> 00:56:48,800
What?

536
00:56:49,840 --> 00:56:51,200
Nothing.

537
00:56:52,640 --> 00:56:54,160
Just remembered

538
00:56:54,320 --> 00:56:56,440
how we used to fight about the lights.

539
00:57:11,320 --> 00:57:12,960
You love arguing with me.

540
00:57:13,800 --> 00:57:15,240
You object to everything.

541
00:57:17,840 --> 00:57:19,360
You're no different.

542
00:57:20,360 --> 00:57:22,280
Once you decide something, that’s it.

543
00:57:23,160 --> 00:57:24,960
See? You’re doing it again.

544
00:57:29,440 --> 00:57:31,440
You’re finally rid of the only person

545
00:57:31,520 --> 00:57:33,040
who argued with you.

546
00:57:35,880 --> 00:57:37,680
I will even miss these little fights.

547
00:57:53,040 --> 00:57:54,200
Good night.

548
00:58:00,280 --> 00:58:01,560
For the last time.

549
00:58:11,920 --> 00:58:13,120
Good night.

550
01:00:42,280 --> 01:00:43,880
I'll miss you so much.

551
01:00:47,200 --> 01:00:48,480
My Mercan.

552
01:02:25,800 --> 01:02:27,240
Good morning.

553
01:02:29,360 --> 01:02:30,760
Good morning.

554
01:02:56,840 --> 01:02:58,280
You left it to the last minute.

555
01:03:01,400 --> 01:03:03,160
I can pack in two minutes.

556
01:03:19,800 --> 01:03:21,360
You…

557
01:03:31,400 --> 01:03:33,800
My men will drive you to the
airport when you’re ready.

558
01:03:39,240 --> 01:03:40,520
No need.

559
01:03:40,760 --> 01:03:42,480
I’ll go on my own.

560
01:03:44,920 --> 01:03:46,360
Okay. As you wish.

561
01:04:31,120 --> 01:04:32,560
Car repair, huh?

562
01:04:32,880 --> 01:04:35,040
This doesn’t look like a garage, Malik.

563
01:04:36,120 --> 01:04:38,040
Let’s see which “mechanic” you’re meeting.

564
01:04:43,320 --> 01:04:45,000
Mr. Malik? Hello.

565
01:04:45,080 --> 01:04:46,600
Hello, Ms. Funda. How are you?

566
01:04:46,680 --> 01:04:47,760
Fine, thanks. How are you?

567
01:04:47,840 --> 01:04:50,800
Good. Thanks. Um... I'll show you the ring.

568
01:04:50,880 --> 01:04:52,440
So, I was thinking of this…

569
01:04:52,600 --> 01:04:53,720
Oh, it's very beautiful.

570
01:04:53,840 --> 01:04:55,760
I like it a lot.

571
01:04:59,760 --> 01:05:01,360
I can’t believe this.

572
01:05:07,040 --> 01:05:08,760
How could you do this to me, Malik?

573
01:05:23,920 --> 01:05:25,440
-I like it a lot. -Same here.

574
01:05:25,600 --> 01:05:27,080
The stone looks great on it.

575
01:05:27,240 --> 01:05:28,440
Well...

576
01:05:29,120 --> 01:05:30,240
Sorry!

577
01:05:30,400 --> 01:05:31,960
Really sorry!

578
01:05:32,320 --> 01:05:34,280
Sorry to interrupt you!

579
01:05:34,760 --> 01:05:36,880
-Çiçek, I... -Shame on you!

580
01:05:37,480 --> 01:05:39,040
Çiçek, I...

581
01:05:40,000 --> 01:05:41,320
Mr. Malik, what’s going on?

582
01:05:41,440 --> 01:05:43,960
-Um, Ms. Funda... -I’ll
tell you what’s going on!

583
01:05:44,040 --> 01:05:46,000
Ms. Funda, I’m sorry.

584
01:05:46,080 --> 01:05:47,320
Let's talk later, okay?

585
01:05:47,560 --> 01:05:48,560
Alright. Fine.

586
01:05:50,480 --> 01:05:53,280
Look at you. “we’ll
talk later”! Unbelievable.

587
01:05:53,760 --> 01:05:55,480
Çiçek, please stop. I'll explain.

588
01:05:55,560 --> 01:05:57,640
Unbelievable. It's like a nightmare.

589
01:05:57,720 --> 01:05:59,520
How could you do this to me, Malik?!

590
01:05:59,680 --> 01:06:01,120
Um, if you listened to me...

591
01:06:01,200 --> 01:06:03,960
Listen to what? More lies?

592
01:06:04,120 --> 01:06:05,720
This is your love?

593
01:06:06,520 --> 01:06:07,880
This.

594
01:06:20,200 --> 01:06:21,640
It was for you.

595
01:06:26,000 --> 01:06:27,720
I didn't imagine it to be like this.

596
01:06:27,920 --> 01:06:29,440
But you ruined your own surprise.

597
01:06:30,960 --> 01:06:32,240
Oh… really?

598
01:06:32,480 --> 01:06:33,960
-I... -You...

599
01:06:34,040 --> 01:06:35,280
misunderstood, right?

600
01:06:37,160 --> 01:06:38,800
-I apologize... -Fine.

601
01:06:39,440 --> 01:06:41,160
Your apology is accepted.

602
01:06:42,760 --> 01:06:44,400
Because I love you so much.

603
01:06:45,360 --> 01:06:48,600
I came all the way from Egypt for you.

604
01:06:49,120 --> 01:06:50,680
For you to be my Çiçek.

605
01:06:56,960 --> 01:06:58,480
You became the flower of my heart…

606
01:07:01,200 --> 01:07:03,200
Will you be the flower of my home too?

607
01:07:03,280 --> 01:07:04,800
Çiçek...

608
01:07:09,320 --> 01:07:10,760
Will you marry me?

609
01:07:22,400 --> 01:07:23,880
Yes! I will.

610
01:07:23,960 --> 01:07:25,800
Yes to all! Yes, yes, yes!

611
01:07:50,640 --> 01:07:52,440
-Malik. -Did you like it?

612
01:07:52,560 --> 01:07:53,920
Loved it so much.

613
01:08:53,720 --> 01:08:55,280
Mom…

614
01:08:57,040 --> 01:08:58,760
It’ll be wonderful there now.

615
01:08:59,080 --> 01:09:01,520
Enjoy yourself.

616
01:09:14,960 --> 01:09:16,280
Dear,

617
01:09:17,040 --> 01:09:18,560
safe travels.

618
01:09:18,880 --> 01:09:20,600
We’ll stay in touch.

619
01:09:22,480 --> 01:09:24,280
Call us anytime.

620
01:09:27,680 --> 01:09:29,160
Come on.

621
01:09:38,560 --> 01:09:40,240
Take care of yourselves, will you?

622
01:09:45,840 --> 01:09:46,920
Come on. Let's go.

623
01:09:47,560 --> 01:09:49,000
I hate long goodbyes.

624
01:09:57,600 --> 01:09:59,880
Take care, Binnaz sister, will you?

625
01:10:00,720 --> 01:10:03,320
You take care far away from home, dear.

626
01:10:03,640 --> 01:10:05,280
You’ve already thinned out so much.

627
01:10:05,360 --> 01:10:06,880
Eat well, don’t waste away.

628
01:10:07,320 --> 01:10:09,640
I’ll weigh you when you get back.

629
01:10:10,840 --> 01:10:12,120
Okay.

630
01:10:13,480 --> 01:10:15,040
Oh my dear angel.

631
01:10:17,360 --> 01:10:18,720
Safe travels.

632
01:10:19,800 --> 01:10:21,200
Thank you.

633
01:10:28,880 --> 01:10:30,280
Dragging it out makes it harder.

634
01:10:30,360 --> 01:10:32,080
I’d better go.

635
01:10:38,160 --> 01:10:41,280
Soon you’re leaving forever.

636
01:10:42,680 --> 01:10:44,880
And I’ve arranged a grand trip for you…

637
01:10:46,280 --> 01:10:48,360
So far away.

638
01:12:34,880 --> 01:12:37,520
I had doubts before…

639
01:12:38,520 --> 01:12:40,000
Not anymore.

640
01:12:41,680 --> 01:12:44,760
Mercan will never come back.

641
01:13:49,800 --> 01:13:51,120
We're ready to go.

642
01:14:23,800 --> 01:14:26,040
If I said, "I changed my mind…"

643
01:14:26,120 --> 01:14:27,400
…who would I even be defying?

644
01:14:41,960 --> 01:14:43,880
Don’t go.

645
01:16:30,640 --> 01:16:31,720
Don't go.

646
01:16:44,280 --> 01:16:45,720
I couldn't tell her to stay.

647
01:17:16,280 --> 01:17:17,760
AAAAAGH!

648
01:17:55,280 --> 01:17:56,280
Come back

649
01:17:56,400 --> 01:17:57,920
Don't leave water fairy.

650
01:20:03,280 --> 01:20:04,960
How many hours have you been gone, Ateş?

651
01:20:05,040 --> 01:20:06,416
You’re not answering your phone either!

652
01:20:06,440 --> 01:20:08,416
I’m sick with worry thinking
something happened to you.

653
01:20:08,440 --> 01:20:09,856
For God’s sake, is this something you do?

654
01:20:09,880 --> 01:20:11,200
Did Nezir kidnap you, set a trap?

655
01:20:11,280 --> 01:20:13,080
Did something happen
to you? I don’t get it.

656
01:20:13,160 --> 01:20:14,200
Why are you doing this?

657
01:20:24,160 --> 01:20:25,560
You didn't leave.

658
01:20:45,080 --> 01:20:46,120
Ateş.

659
01:20:52,080 --> 01:20:53,520
Leave me alone, Cemal.

660
01:20:55,600 --> 01:20:56,880
You don't look too good.

661
01:20:59,000 --> 01:21:00,320
I’m not okay, Cemal!

662
01:21:00,720 --> 01:21:01,880
Not at all.

663
01:21:01,960 --> 01:21:03,280
I’m actually a mess!

664
01:21:09,600 --> 01:21:11,280
Please, just don’t ask me anything.

665
01:21:13,840 --> 01:21:15,400
You can still go after her.

666
01:21:18,040 --> 01:21:19,160
It’s too late.

667
01:21:21,200 --> 01:21:24,520
It’s never too late for anything,
Ateş. Better than regretting it later.

668
01:21:32,440 --> 01:21:34,160
While you love each other so much...

669
01:21:35,400 --> 01:21:37,160
How is this going to work like this?

670
01:21:37,240 --> 01:21:38,520
May God help you.

671
01:25:13,480 --> 01:25:14,920
What am I doing?

672
01:25:36,680 --> 01:25:37,920
She kept it.

673
01:25:57,920 --> 01:25:59,240
It’ll pass…

674
01:26:03,320 --> 01:26:04,680
It has to pass.

675
01:26:16,360 --> 01:26:18,640
I still can’t believe it…

676
01:26:19,480 --> 01:26:22,320
If this is a dream, Malik,
I never want to wake up.

677
01:26:24,000 --> 01:26:25,160
Çiçek,

678
01:26:26,560 --> 01:26:28,440
I’ll make every day God gives us

679
01:26:29,200 --> 01:26:30,840
feel like a dream.

680
01:26:31,040 --> 01:26:32,480
I promise, my darling.

681
01:26:43,440 --> 01:26:45,240
I don’t want to wait any longer.

682
01:26:46,240 --> 01:26:48,960
Let’s talk to your mother and
Berat and tell them everything.

683
01:26:51,480 --> 01:26:52,760
The sooner, the better.

684
01:26:58,000 --> 01:26:59,720
Ever since you proposed,

685
01:26:59,800 --> 01:27:02,040
I haven’t felt my feet touch the ground…

686
01:27:02,120 --> 01:27:05,240
That "marry me" keeps echoing in my ears…

687
01:27:48,160 --> 01:27:49,800
I see you’re in a good mood today.

688
01:27:51,440 --> 01:27:53,720
Does Mercan leaving have
anything to do with that?

689
01:27:54,880 --> 01:27:56,800
I didn’t even say a word, Cemal.

690
01:27:58,720 --> 01:28:00,840
How did you jump to that conclusion?

691
01:28:02,520 --> 01:28:06,120
I know you well, Aslı…

692
01:28:06,600 --> 01:28:08,520
Even better than you think.

693
01:28:10,360 --> 01:28:11,680
Don’t be so sure.

694
01:28:39,560 --> 01:28:43,360
Ateş... How about we go out tonight?

695
01:28:43,560 --> 01:28:45,920
The three of us haven’t
gone out together in ages.

696
01:28:49,680 --> 01:28:50,920
That’d be nice…

697
01:28:51,240 --> 01:28:52,760
We could all spend time together.

698
01:28:52,840 --> 01:28:53,960
Seriously…

699
01:28:54,320 --> 01:28:55,800
This mansion is suffocating me.

700
01:28:56,760 --> 01:28:59,920
It’s like the evil of everyone
living here has seeped into the walls.

701
01:29:03,560 --> 01:29:04,840
Ateş?

702
01:29:06,480 --> 01:29:08,200
I’ve got work to do.

703
01:29:08,680 --> 01:29:09,720
You two go.

704
01:29:10,920 --> 01:29:12,840
You’re always the buzzkill.

705
01:29:23,440 --> 01:29:25,200
The guy from London still hasn’t called.

706
01:29:26,240 --> 01:29:27,920
The plane should’ve landed by now.

707
01:29:30,720 --> 01:29:32,000
Why don’t you call him?

708
01:29:37,960 --> 01:29:39,480
He’s calling…

709
01:29:41,040 --> 01:29:43,360
-Hello? -I'm at the airport, brother.

710
01:29:43,480 --> 01:29:44,960
The lady didn’t get off the plane.

711
01:29:47,920 --> 01:29:49,760
What do you mean she
didn’t get off the plane?

712
01:29:49,840 --> 01:29:51,480
How is that possible?

713
01:30:52,880 --> 01:30:54,800
I think she ran away.

714
01:30:55,200 --> 01:30:56,560
Aslı, what are you saying?

715
01:30:57,800 --> 01:30:59,360
Why are you snapping at me?

716
01:30:59,440 --> 01:31:00,920
Did I say something wrong?

717
01:31:01,640 --> 01:31:04,000
She got her chance and took off.

718
01:31:05,040 --> 01:31:07,120
She’s probably not coming back.

719
01:31:08,080 --> 01:31:09,960
And who cares anyway?

720
01:31:10,920 --> 01:31:14,280
Our priority is her
father, not the daughter.

721
01:31:19,480 --> 01:31:20,760
Mercan never got on the plane.

722
01:31:21,760 --> 01:31:24,800
Ateş, she probably didn’t
even make it to the airport.

723
01:31:26,480 --> 01:31:28,000
What are you saying, Cemal?

724
01:31:29,240 --> 01:31:31,040
Could Haydar be involved?

725
01:31:35,600 --> 01:31:36,960
I can’t reach Mercan!

726
01:31:37,520 --> 01:31:39,080
Have you talked to her?

727
01:31:41,200 --> 01:31:43,280
Shouldn’t she have landed by now?

728
01:31:51,360 --> 01:31:52,960
Mercan’s phone is off…

729
01:31:53,840 --> 01:31:55,240
Ah!

730
01:31:55,320 --> 01:31:58,200
- This is your doing, isn’t it?!
- What the hell are you talking about?

731
01:31:58,280 --> 01:31:59,560
She never got on the plane!

732
01:31:59,680 --> 01:32:01,560
What do you mean she
never got on the plane?

733
01:32:02,840 --> 01:32:05,440
Don’t play dumb with
me! Where did you take her?

734
01:32:05,640 --> 01:32:06,800
Have you lost your mind?

735
01:32:06,880 --> 01:32:10,200
Why would I kidnap her when
she finally got away from you!

736
01:32:10,280 --> 01:32:11,640
For God’s sake! Stop it!

737
01:32:12,480 --> 01:32:13,600
Mercan is missing…

738
01:32:13,680 --> 01:32:16,080
Why are you two fighting
instead of looking for her?

739
01:32:17,480 --> 01:32:19,760
I’m not the one who has
to answer here, you are!

740
01:32:20,080 --> 01:32:22,680
Tell me where my daughter
is! What did you do to her?

741
01:32:26,000 --> 01:32:27,200
What’s going on here?

742
01:32:28,520 --> 01:32:29,760
Mercan is missing!

743
01:32:38,480 --> 01:32:41,280
Let’s find the taxi driver and
figure out where Mercan got off.

744
01:32:41,360 --> 01:32:43,800
Let's check all the cameras
on the way to the airport.

745
01:32:43,920 --> 01:32:46,320
If we have to, we’ll
search all of Istanbul, Cemal.

746
01:32:48,000 --> 01:32:50,240
What makes you think she’s missing?

747
01:32:51,480 --> 01:32:53,920
Maybe she went to her ex.

748
01:32:55,240 --> 01:32:58,360
Her mind was always on
that useless man anyway.

749
01:32:59,880 --> 01:33:01,960
God knows, they’re
probably together right now.

750
01:33:08,680 --> 01:33:09,960
Nezir…

751
01:33:12,120 --> 01:33:13,800
How did I not think of him?

752
01:33:20,760 --> 01:33:21,880
Move.

753
01:33:30,880 --> 01:33:33,600
What have you done this time?

754
01:33:38,320 --> 01:33:39,680
I did what had to be done.

755
01:33:47,800 --> 01:33:49,320
With every passing second,

756
01:33:49,680 --> 01:33:51,840
she gets a little closer to death.

757
01:33:53,920 --> 01:33:55,200
Aslı, she was already leaving.

758
01:33:55,280 --> 01:33:57,880
Why would you kidnap her
and bring trouble on yourself?

759
01:34:01,120 --> 01:34:02,720
I couldn’t leave it to chance.

760
01:34:03,400 --> 01:34:04,840
She could’ve come back.

761
01:34:05,360 --> 01:34:06,840
She’s obsessed with Ateş.

762
01:34:07,960 --> 01:34:10,040
And why are you so worried anyway?

763
01:34:10,800 --> 01:34:13,280
You know this girl is
nothing but trouble for us.

764
01:34:14,800 --> 01:34:17,280
Aslı… How did you become like this?

765
01:34:18,880 --> 01:34:20,560
I’ve always been like this, Mom…

766
01:34:22,640 --> 01:34:24,240
And I learned it from you.

767
01:34:25,560 --> 01:34:27,160
I carry your genes.

768
01:34:28,760 --> 01:34:30,760
Didn’t you raise us on revenge?

769
01:34:31,880 --> 01:34:33,160
Didn’t you poison all of us

770
01:34:33,280 --> 01:34:35,800
with your hatred all these years?

771
01:34:36,800 --> 01:34:38,520
Didn’t you say

772
01:34:38,600 --> 01:34:41,480
"we won’t show the Yıldırıms
any mercy" on our way here?

773
01:34:43,360 --> 01:34:46,440
We made all these plans… We came this far.

774
01:34:47,040 --> 01:34:49,080
And now what I did is the problem?

775
01:34:50,120 --> 01:34:54,520
What I’ve done is tiny
next to what you’ve done.

776
01:34:54,760 --> 01:34:58,160
I told you, "Whatever needs to be
done, Ateş and I will handle it."

777
01:34:58,360 --> 01:35:00,520
I never wanted you involved.

778
01:35:01,320 --> 01:35:02,760
And I made my choice.

779
01:35:03,000 --> 01:35:04,360
I got involved.

780
01:35:07,440 --> 01:35:08,760
Ever since your father died,

781
01:35:08,840 --> 01:35:13,960
I’ve been fighting for you to have
a clean future, a privileged life.

782
01:35:14,040 --> 01:35:16,000
And look what you’re doing.

783
01:35:16,600 --> 01:35:18,720
Call them. Tell them to let her go.

784
01:35:19,200 --> 01:35:20,560
No.

785
01:35:21,200 --> 01:35:23,600
I’m getting rid of that girl today.

786
01:35:38,360 --> 01:35:40,520
It looks great, Zehra.

787
01:35:44,680 --> 01:35:46,760
Take a look… tell me if you like it.

788
01:35:47,560 --> 01:35:49,480
I can’t make it as
well as your mother, but…

789
01:35:54,160 --> 01:35:55,800
Zehra...

790
01:35:56,160 --> 01:35:58,760
The fact that you even thought
of it is enough. Thanks a lot.

791
01:35:58,840 --> 01:36:00,640
But you really shouldn’t have bothered.

792
01:36:02,200 --> 01:36:03,440
Yummy! Yummy!

793
01:36:05,840 --> 01:36:07,240
You’re already working so hard.

794
01:36:07,320 --> 01:36:09,160
And you even made me dessert.

795
01:36:09,880 --> 01:36:11,520
Thank you so much.

796
01:36:11,800 --> 01:36:14,320
I don’t get tired when
I’m doing something for you.

797
01:36:16,120 --> 01:36:17,840
And you’re exhausted too.

798
01:36:17,960 --> 01:36:21,360
I see you running around day and night.

799
01:36:21,880 --> 01:36:23,560
The garden, the shopping…

800
01:36:24,640 --> 01:36:26,400
everything falls on you.

801
01:36:27,440 --> 01:36:28,960
It makes me sad, Berat.

802
01:36:30,600 --> 01:36:33,200
Malik only deals with cars,

803
01:36:34,200 --> 01:36:36,520
and all the burden is
on you. It’s not fair.

804
01:36:40,440 --> 01:36:42,680
Well… yeah, that’s true, Zehra.

805
01:36:45,680 --> 01:36:49,360
But Malik was hired as a driver.

806
01:36:51,480 --> 01:36:56,360
Everyone except Nermin and
Müzeyyen drives themselves anyway.

807
01:36:57,800 --> 01:37:01,040
And they barely leave the house.

808
01:37:02,960 --> 01:37:05,560
Malik just wanders around doing nothing.

809
01:37:07,920 --> 01:37:09,240
You should talk to him.

810
01:37:09,720 --> 01:37:11,120
Make him help you.

811
01:37:13,000 --> 01:37:14,240
Oh, no.

812
01:37:14,600 --> 01:37:16,840
Your mother’s coming, she
shouldn’t see us together.

813
01:37:17,000 --> 01:37:18,720
Go on, hurry, go!

814
01:37:27,160 --> 01:37:28,480
Hello.

815
01:37:29,120 --> 01:37:30,680
Would you like some desert?

816
01:37:31,120 --> 01:37:32,400
I made it.

817
01:37:32,920 --> 01:37:34,440
No, thanks.

818
01:37:36,480 --> 01:37:38,080
Did something happen?

819
01:37:39,000 --> 01:37:40,560
You look a little upset.

820
01:37:41,120 --> 01:37:43,280
Mrs. Mercan is nowhere to be found.

821
01:37:43,360 --> 01:37:45,160
I can’t stop thinking about her.

822
01:37:46,400 --> 01:37:47,720
Oh...

823
01:37:50,840 --> 01:37:53,480
You can’t even enjoy
your daughter’s happiness,

824
01:37:53,560 --> 01:37:55,520
and you’re worrying about Mrs. Mercan?

825
01:37:56,920 --> 01:37:58,800
She should be fine, don’t worry.

826
01:38:00,720 --> 01:38:02,280
What happiness?

827
01:38:03,600 --> 01:38:05,400
Her engagement, of course.

828
01:38:05,520 --> 01:38:06,800
She’s wearing a ring…

829
01:38:07,240 --> 01:38:08,840
What ring? There’s no such thing.

830
01:38:09,000 --> 01:38:10,440
Where did you get that from?

831
01:38:14,120 --> 01:38:17,440
Oh… so you decided to hide it?

832
01:38:18,240 --> 01:38:19,360
Fine, no problem.

833
01:38:20,040 --> 01:38:21,200
I won’t tell anyone.

834
01:38:22,280 --> 01:38:23,720
But, um...

835
01:38:24,600 --> 01:38:26,800
Çiçek’s been a bit cold to me lately.

836
01:38:27,440 --> 01:38:29,800
If you congratulate her for me...

837
01:38:30,320 --> 01:38:31,360
Would you?

838
01:38:31,960 --> 01:38:34,720
Say what you’re trying to say properly!

839
01:38:34,800 --> 01:38:37,720
What ring? What congratulations?
What are you talking about?

840
01:38:38,680 --> 01:38:40,520
I just… I don't know.

841
01:38:41,640 --> 01:38:43,920
I saw a ring on her finger.

842
01:38:45,680 --> 01:38:47,160
Oh no…

843
01:38:48,720 --> 01:38:50,840
Was she planning to surprise you?

844
01:38:51,920 --> 01:38:54,760
Did I ruin it? I'm so sorry.

845
01:39:00,200 --> 01:39:04,040
Um... Mrs. Nermin wants water.

846
01:39:10,840 --> 01:39:12,640
Mom?

847
01:39:18,400 --> 01:39:19,760
Mommy.

848
01:39:39,320 --> 01:39:41,120
What the hell? You think this is a barn?

849
01:39:44,120 --> 01:39:45,680
Where is Mercan?

850
01:39:46,640 --> 01:39:48,440
-Speak! -Let go!

851
01:39:51,440 --> 01:39:52,960
-Speak! -ghhk…

852
01:39:53,040 --> 01:39:55,200
Tell me where she is right now!

853
01:39:56,680 --> 01:39:58,240
I swear I’ll kill you!

854
01:39:58,480 --> 01:40:01,040
Look, I'll kill you. I’m serious.

855
01:40:01,600 --> 01:40:02,760
Let go.

856
01:40:09,240 --> 01:40:10,480
Didn’t she go to London?

857
01:40:11,960 --> 01:40:13,640
Why are you looking for Mercan?

858
01:40:14,040 --> 01:40:15,360
What happened to her?

859
01:40:16,680 --> 01:40:18,400
You’re going to tell me.

860
01:40:18,840 --> 01:40:20,840
Tell me what happened to Mercan.

861
01:40:21,640 --> 01:40:22,680
Where is she?

862
01:40:22,800 --> 01:40:24,440
Mercan never went to London.

863
01:40:26,400 --> 01:40:27,680
She did not?

864
01:40:33,080 --> 01:40:35,280
All I wanted was for
her to get away from you!

865
01:40:36,120 --> 01:40:37,600
Why would I stop her?

866
01:40:39,760 --> 01:40:42,000
If you’re...

867
01:40:43,120 --> 01:40:44,800
If you're lying to me...

868
01:41:28,200 --> 01:41:29,920
She still hasn’t woken up, ma’am.

869
01:41:31,040 --> 01:41:33,840
You’re not leaving until
you’re sure she’s dead.

870
01:41:34,080 --> 01:41:35,160
Don’t worry.

871
01:41:35,240 --> 01:41:36,440
I’m watching you.

872
01:41:36,920 --> 01:41:38,480
Her death shouldn’t be easy.

873
01:41:39,520 --> 01:41:40,840
I want her to die in panic…

874
01:41:41,040 --> 01:41:42,840
in struggle.

875
01:41:43,800 --> 01:41:46,400
Therefore, the water needs to
rise millimeter by millimeter.

876
01:41:51,600 --> 01:41:52,800
What a psychopath…

877
01:42:23,360 --> 01:42:25,080
What is this?

878
01:42:27,560 --> 01:42:28,800
Is anyone there?!

879
01:42:28,920 --> 01:42:30,440
Somebody help me!

880
01:42:31,440 --> 01:42:33,040
Is anyone there?

881
01:42:35,720 --> 01:42:37,120
Is anyone there?

882
01:42:44,160 --> 01:42:45,840
Somebody help me!

883
01:42:46,880 --> 01:42:48,280
Is anyone there?

884
01:42:50,800 --> 01:42:51,920
Alright, thanks.

885
01:42:52,840 --> 01:42:54,160
What did he say? Tell me.

886
01:42:54,360 --> 01:42:55,936
The taxi driver never
returned to the station.

887
01:42:55,960 --> 01:42:57,840
We’re checking every camera on the route.

888
01:42:57,920 --> 01:42:59,720
Maybe she left on her own, Ateş.

889
01:43:01,000 --> 01:43:02,240
I don’t think so, Cemal.

890
01:43:02,640 --> 01:43:05,840
Mercan isn’t someone who’d
leave her family worried.

891
01:43:06,280 --> 01:43:07,320
Then what could it be?

892
01:43:07,560 --> 01:43:08,840
The man who shot her is dead…

893
01:43:09,480 --> 01:43:11,840
Who else hates her enough to do something?

894
01:43:15,680 --> 01:43:17,360
There’s… Mother Müzeyyen, of course.

895
01:43:18,000 --> 01:43:19,360
But no way.

896
01:43:19,680 --> 01:43:21,040
She wouldn't do such a thing.

897
01:43:21,920 --> 01:43:23,960
Today, they were
actually so happy she left.

898
01:43:26,120 --> 01:43:27,680
Then who?

899
01:43:29,400 --> 01:43:31,640
It can’t be the victims
on Haydar’s smuggling list.

900
01:43:31,920 --> 01:43:33,720
Most of them survive thanks to your help.

901
01:43:34,040 --> 01:43:36,280
They’re poor, helpless
people. They wouldn't do.

902
01:43:36,760 --> 01:43:39,360
I’ll knock on every door if I have to.

903
01:43:45,080 --> 01:43:46,160
Wait. Not like this.

904
01:43:46,240 --> 01:43:48,080
-Stay calm until then. -I can't!

905
01:43:48,280 --> 01:43:49,960
I can’t stay calm!

906
01:43:50,080 --> 01:43:51,280
You have to.

907
01:43:51,520 --> 01:43:53,400
She needs you. We need you.

908
01:43:53,680 --> 01:43:55,360
Wait for the camera footage first.

909
01:43:58,880 --> 01:44:00,680
AAAAAGH!

910
01:44:09,400 --> 01:44:10,560
This is my fault.

911
01:44:13,480 --> 01:44:14,800
I shouldn’t have let her go.

912
01:44:18,920 --> 01:44:20,440
If something happens to her…

913
01:44:23,160 --> 01:44:24,560
It’s not only your fault.

914
01:44:24,960 --> 01:44:26,120
It’s our fault too.

915
01:44:27,280 --> 01:44:28,840
We pushed you too hard.

916
01:44:29,480 --> 01:44:31,800
You thought sending her
away was the only solution…

917
01:44:35,760 --> 01:44:39,280
We didn’t realize your
heart would go with her.

918
01:44:46,040 --> 01:44:49,480
Sitting here doing nothing
is driving me insane.

919
01:45:50,880 --> 01:45:52,320
Help!

920
01:45:55,000 --> 01:45:56,880
Somebody hear me?!

921
01:46:16,320 --> 01:46:17,840
What if I never see you again?

922
01:46:29,320 --> 01:46:31,000
What if something happens to you?

923
01:46:38,080 --> 01:46:39,280
Where are you…

924
01:46:41,120 --> 01:46:42,400
where are you?

925
01:47:26,840 --> 01:47:28,240
Help!

926
01:47:41,320 --> 01:47:43,040
Look at her trying to escape.

927
01:47:44,400 --> 01:47:46,960
Watching her die is
going to be so satisfying.

928
01:48:02,640 --> 01:48:03,880
Where is Mercan?

929
01:48:04,520 --> 01:48:06,120
What did you do to her?

930
01:48:07,080 --> 01:48:08,680
First answer:

931
01:48:09,000 --> 01:48:11,840
I don’t know where she
is, and I don’t care.

932
01:48:12,760 --> 01:48:14,240
Second answer:

933
01:48:14,840 --> 01:48:16,520
I didn’t do anything.

934
01:48:17,160 --> 01:48:20,400
Why would I bother when
Ateş already kicked her out?

935
01:48:21,360 --> 01:48:23,640
All I wanted was for her to disappear.

936
01:48:24,680 --> 01:48:26,240
You’re capable of anything.

937
01:48:26,320 --> 01:48:29,600
Look who’s talking.

938
01:48:30,600 --> 01:48:32,160
You’re no saint either.

939
01:48:33,360 --> 01:48:34,880
Don’t act superior, Nezir.

940
01:48:35,480 --> 01:48:37,240
We’re cut from the same cloth.

941
01:48:37,840 --> 01:48:40,880
And who knows, maybe one
of Haydar’s enemies did it.

942
01:48:49,920 --> 01:48:51,480
For God's sake!

943
01:48:56,640 --> 01:48:58,160
What are you doing here, man?

944
01:48:58,920 --> 01:49:01,840
You think we’re joking around?
You think we’re playing games?

945
01:49:01,920 --> 01:49:03,240
Look. Around this mansion,

946
01:49:03,440 --> 01:49:04,720
anywhere near Mercan,

947
01:49:05,280 --> 01:49:08,000
anywhere near Aslı... Didn’t
I tell you I better not see you?

948
01:49:08,080 --> 01:49:10,960
If the beating you got wasn’t enough,

949
01:49:11,120 --> 01:49:13,280
I swear I can continue where Ateş left off.

950
01:49:16,080 --> 01:49:19,280
I came to ask if there’s
any news about Mercan, bro.

951
01:49:19,360 --> 01:49:21,400
You can't. You've got
nothing to do with that.

952
01:49:21,480 --> 01:49:22,720
Now get out.

953
01:49:23,280 --> 01:49:24,760
I came to see Haydar.

954
01:49:25,480 --> 01:49:27,120
I’m not leaving without seeing him.

955
01:49:28,440 --> 01:49:30,000
You’ve got ten minutes.

956
01:49:31,040 --> 01:49:32,760
If I see you after that,

957
01:49:33,040 --> 01:49:35,200
I swear I'll throw you
out like a garbage bag.

958
01:49:36,440 --> 01:49:37,880
You too, Aslı. Get inside.

959
01:49:42,600 --> 01:49:44,160
What’s wrong with you?

960
01:49:47,160 --> 01:49:50,040
Why are you talking to me
like you’re giving orders?

961
01:49:50,360 --> 01:49:51,400
So, Aslı...

962
01:49:51,480 --> 01:49:53,296
You’re spending too
much time around this man.

963
01:49:53,320 --> 01:49:55,840
What business do you have with
him? Stay away from that man.

964
01:49:57,080 --> 01:49:58,760
What business would I have with him?

965
01:49:58,920 --> 01:50:00,560
He was asking about Mercan…

966
01:50:01,040 --> 01:50:02,640
And who do you think you are?

967
01:50:03,000 --> 01:50:04,480
You can’t question me!

968
01:50:04,840 --> 01:50:06,400
I talk to whoever I want.

969
01:50:11,440 --> 01:50:12,800
Hello?

970
01:50:22,280 --> 01:50:23,760
Got it.

971
01:50:24,960 --> 01:50:26,240
What happened?

972
01:50:26,400 --> 01:50:28,280
Nothing, Aslı.

973
01:50:43,080 --> 01:50:44,440
Everything’s fine.

974
01:51:15,720 --> 01:51:17,240
Let's go.

975
01:51:17,880 --> 01:51:19,560
Let's check these.

976
01:51:27,400 --> 01:51:28,440
No...

977
01:51:28,520 --> 01:51:30,880
No, my daughter wouldn’t
do something like that.

978
01:51:31,840 --> 01:51:32,920
Oh.

979
01:51:34,080 --> 01:51:35,480
It's not here.

980
01:51:36,520 --> 01:51:38,560
This is empty.

981
01:51:53,120 --> 01:51:54,440
They're just beads.

982
01:51:54,920 --> 01:51:56,200
It’s not here either.

983
01:51:57,000 --> 01:51:59,240
There’s nothing.

984
01:52:00,000 --> 01:52:02,600
No, no. My daughter wouldn’t
do something like that.

985
01:52:03,080 --> 01:52:04,360
Can't be.

986
01:52:05,080 --> 01:52:07,520
Ugh, stupid me. I listened to Zehra.

987
01:52:07,720 --> 01:52:10,280
I believed that snake
and searched her room.

988
01:52:10,680 --> 01:52:12,120
See, there's nothing here.

989
01:52:12,920 --> 01:52:15,520
Let me put these back. If
Çiçek sees, she'll get mad.

990
01:52:20,160 --> 01:52:21,720
Zehra. Ah, that Zehra…

991
01:52:21,960 --> 01:52:23,280
She’s stirring everything up.

992
01:52:32,000 --> 01:52:33,680
We’re wronging Çiçek.

993
01:52:37,240 --> 01:52:38,640
Hm...

994
01:52:38,800 --> 01:52:40,680
Her purse is here too.

995
01:52:42,000 --> 01:52:43,480
Let me check this too.

996
01:52:43,920 --> 01:52:45,440
There shouldn’t be anything in it.

997
01:52:45,600 --> 01:52:47,080
No. Why would there be?

998
01:52:52,600 --> 01:52:53,800
Oh… what’s this?

999
01:53:13,760 --> 01:53:14,840
Oh...

1000
01:53:16,200 --> 01:53:18,080
Çiçek… what have you done?

1001
01:53:20,200 --> 01:53:21,720
Çiçek, what have you done, dear?

1002
01:53:23,280 --> 01:53:24,640
Oh no…

1003
01:53:25,920 --> 01:53:27,320
What am I going to do now?

1004
01:53:27,480 --> 01:53:29,280
What are we going to do?

1005
01:53:32,280 --> 01:53:33,480
What trouble is this…

1006
01:53:34,000 --> 01:53:35,440
What trouble is this…

1007
01:53:38,680 --> 01:53:40,640
Oh no! Is that Çiçek coming?

1008
01:54:15,720 --> 01:54:16,920
What do you want?

1009
01:54:17,760 --> 01:54:20,040
Um, I saw Çiçek in the back garden,

1010
01:54:20,840 --> 01:54:21,960
rushing somewhere.

1011
01:54:22,040 --> 01:54:23,800
I got worried. Is everything okay?

1012
01:54:24,760 --> 01:54:25,880
Where was she going?

1013
01:54:26,120 --> 01:54:28,720
I don’t know… she just looked in a hurry.

1014
01:54:30,200 --> 01:54:31,600
Step aside.

1015
01:54:43,040 --> 01:54:44,400
Stupid Çiçek…

1016
01:54:45,040 --> 01:54:47,320
did you think you could compete with me?

1017
01:55:01,360 --> 01:55:02,920
I just can’t wrap my head around it.

1018
01:55:03,000 --> 01:55:05,000
Where could this girl have disappeared to?

1019
01:55:05,880 --> 01:55:07,080
Haydar...

1020
01:55:08,160 --> 01:55:11,280
I can’t stop thinking about
what you said to Müzeyyen today.

1021
01:55:12,800 --> 01:55:14,840
Could she have done something to Mercan?

1022
01:55:16,400 --> 01:55:18,920
At first I suspected her too, but…

1023
01:55:20,080 --> 01:55:22,000
no, it doesn’t make much sense.

1024
01:55:22,080 --> 01:55:24,600
They sent her away.
Why would they hurt her?

1025
01:55:29,560 --> 01:55:32,280
You can expect anything
from Müzeyyen. That's why.

1026
01:55:32,440 --> 01:55:35,720
She’d do it just to hurt us.

1027
01:55:36,520 --> 01:55:38,760
She’s been hostile for
no reason from the start.

1028
01:55:41,160 --> 01:55:43,000
I don’t think Müzeyyen did it either.

1029
01:55:44,920 --> 01:55:47,080
Then where's Mercan?

1030
01:55:47,680 --> 01:55:49,120
Who would want anything from her?

1031
01:55:52,280 --> 01:55:53,880
Talk to Demet too.

1032
01:55:54,680 --> 01:55:56,320
Maybe she knows something.

1033
01:55:57,800 --> 01:55:59,040
I asked. She doesn’t.

1034
01:56:00,720 --> 01:56:02,000
But don’t worry.

1035
01:56:02,080 --> 01:56:03,400
I’ll do everything I can.

1036
01:56:06,200 --> 01:56:07,680
Maybe they’re right…

1037
01:56:08,240 --> 01:56:09,720
maybe she just left.

1038
01:56:10,040 --> 01:56:12,120
Ran away from everything... from all of us.

1039
01:56:12,840 --> 01:56:14,080
She just left.

1040
01:56:15,240 --> 01:56:16,600
Maybe.

1041
01:56:17,480 --> 01:56:18,920
She’s tired…

1042
01:56:20,080 --> 01:56:22,320
She’s been carrying a
huge weight on her shoulders.

1043
01:56:24,000 --> 01:56:25,640
She married someone she didn’t want.

1044
01:56:29,920 --> 01:56:31,520
And Ateş… he really wore her down.

1045
01:56:32,080 --> 01:56:35,400
And on top of that, she had to deal
with a mother in law like Müzeyyen.

1046
01:56:36,600 --> 01:56:37,960
But this is Mercan.

1047
01:56:39,080 --> 01:56:41,120
She wouldn’t leave without saying a word.

1048
01:56:41,360 --> 01:56:43,640
I know my daughter.

1049
01:56:45,280 --> 01:56:48,280
We need to find out
right away what Ateş knows.

1050
01:57:01,040 --> 01:57:03,280
I don’t understand it, Malik.

1051
01:57:03,760 --> 01:57:07,000
Mrs. Mercan would never disappear
without telling her family.

1052
01:57:07,280 --> 01:57:08,880
I’m certain something bad happened.

1053
01:57:08,960 --> 01:57:10,240
As sure as I know my own name.

1054
01:57:10,800 --> 01:57:12,120
Don't worry.

1055
01:57:12,920 --> 01:57:15,960
Whatever happened… I’m
sure Mr. Ateş will find her.

1056
01:57:16,480 --> 01:57:17,880
I hope so.

1057
01:57:19,520 --> 01:57:20,840
Don’t worry.

1058
01:57:21,880 --> 01:57:23,920
Everything is getting too heavy.

1059
01:57:24,160 --> 01:57:25,760
We're so tense.

1060
01:57:26,320 --> 01:57:27,840
We haven’t had a single peaceful day.

1061
01:57:28,360 --> 01:57:29,640
We will, my Çiçek.

1062
01:57:29,840 --> 01:57:31,440
We’re so close now.

1063
01:57:37,840 --> 01:57:39,240
Çiçek!

1064
01:57:48,000 --> 01:57:49,080
Mom…

1065
01:57:49,160 --> 01:57:50,520
We’ll settle this at home!

1066
01:57:50,600 --> 01:57:51,720
Get here.

1067
01:57:52,080 --> 01:57:54,440
- Binnaz aunt.
- I will never let you marry my daughter!

1068
01:57:54,520 --> 01:57:55,520
Got it?!

1069
01:57:55,600 --> 01:57:57,640
This marriage will never happen! Got it?!

1070
01:57:57,840 --> 01:58:00,000
I will never let you marry my daughter!

1071
01:58:10,000 --> 01:58:11,600
Come on, girl. Move!

1072
01:58:12,040 --> 01:58:13,360
Binnaz aunt.

1073
01:58:15,000 --> 01:58:16,320
Move!

1074
01:58:31,600 --> 01:58:33,080
The car that cut me off...

1075
01:58:33,560 --> 01:58:35,320
The car that cut me off was black,

1076
01:58:35,600 --> 01:58:37,480
but I panicked and
couldn't catch the plate.

1077
01:58:38,080 --> 01:58:40,720
Two men got out wearing ski masks.

1078
01:58:40,880 --> 01:58:42,080
They had guns.

1079
01:58:46,280 --> 01:58:49,080
They threatened me and took my taxi.

1080
01:58:49,680 --> 01:58:51,160
I wanted to help the girl,

1081
01:58:51,720 --> 01:58:53,120
but they held a gun to my head.

1082
01:58:57,720 --> 01:58:59,000
I couldn’t do anything.

1083
01:58:59,240 --> 01:59:01,600
- Why didn’t you go to the police?
- I was scared.

1084
01:59:01,760 --> 01:59:03,560
They threatened my kids.

1085
01:59:03,920 --> 01:59:06,560
They knew where I worked…

1086
01:59:07,320 --> 01:59:09,080
That's why I couldn't do anything.

1087
01:59:09,560 --> 01:59:11,000
I didn’t think about myself,

1088
01:59:11,200 --> 01:59:12,680
only my children...

1089
01:59:13,360 --> 01:59:15,600
You picked the passenger
up from this mansion!

1090
01:59:16,040 --> 01:59:18,600
Even if you didn’t go to the
police, you could’ve come to us!

1091
01:59:18,680 --> 01:59:22,760
Alright, bro. It’s not his fault.
He was scared, that’s obvious.

1092
01:59:26,120 --> 01:59:28,080
And he told us enough to help.

1093
01:59:29,520 --> 01:59:30,880
Alright, brother. Thanks.

1094
01:59:31,040 --> 01:59:32,800
Our guys will take you wherever you need.

1095
01:59:32,960 --> 01:59:36,400
- Don’t worry, they’ll find your taxi too.
- Thank you. God bless you.

1096
01:59:37,440 --> 01:59:39,640
- May God gift you what you need.
- Thank you.

1097
01:59:46,640 --> 01:59:48,640
They kidnapped Mercan
right under our noses.

1098
01:59:53,880 --> 01:59:55,440
What if something happens to her?

1099
01:59:55,520 --> 01:59:57,160
Nothing will happen, bro!

1100
01:59:57,280 --> 01:59:58,840
Keep your mind at ease.

1101
02:00:00,560 --> 02:00:02,000
Nothing will happen.

1102
02:00:02,520 --> 02:00:04,360
I won’t let it.

1103
02:00:11,560 --> 02:00:13,000
Hello?

1104
02:00:21,040 --> 02:00:23,960
The traffic and security
footage just came in.

1105
02:00:24,040 --> 02:00:25,240
Let's take a look.

1106
02:00:25,520 --> 02:00:28,000
Splitting up the work will make it easier.

1107
02:01:12,960 --> 02:01:14,760
Stop!

1108
02:01:15,360 --> 02:01:17,080
Go back a little.

1109
02:01:18,480 --> 02:01:20,040
Stop!

1110
02:01:20,720 --> 02:01:22,400
There's a car coming out from there.

1111
02:01:27,320 --> 02:01:28,960
That means there’s a road in the woods.

1112
02:01:29,760 --> 02:01:31,680
And we spent all night trying to figure out

1113
02:01:31,760 --> 02:01:33,560
where the taxi went, on the main road.

1114
02:01:33,640 --> 02:01:34,880
It went into the forest.

1115
02:01:37,040 --> 02:01:38,400
Exactly.

1116
02:01:39,640 --> 02:01:42,120
If we hadn’t noticed
that car, we’d never know…

1117
02:01:42,680 --> 02:01:44,120
Let’s check the map.

1118
02:01:52,680 --> 02:01:57,240
There are only a few factories
and old warehouses in that area.

1119
02:02:19,480 --> 02:02:21,120
Not a word to anyone.

1120
02:02:21,480 --> 02:02:23,400
-No one. -Don't worry.

1121
02:02:27,680 --> 02:02:29,800
What's up? You two were here all night?

1122
02:02:29,880 --> 02:02:31,400
Yes.

1123
02:02:31,480 --> 02:02:33,160
Did you find anything?

1124
02:02:36,640 --> 02:02:37,960
Nothing certain yet, Mother.

1125
02:02:38,040 --> 02:02:40,440
If we find something,
you'll know. Don't worry.

1126
02:03:17,840 --> 02:03:19,720
Who are you?

1127
02:03:20,080 --> 02:03:22,560
You’re even afraid to
show your face, aren’t you?

1128
02:04:03,120 --> 02:04:04,680
They’re looking for me everywhere!

1129
02:04:05,000 --> 02:04:06,440
Make no mistake, they'll find me.

1130
02:04:07,920 --> 02:04:09,560
Let me go. I won’t tell anyone.

1131
02:04:10,400 --> 02:04:11,960
Get me out of here!

1132
02:04:14,520 --> 02:04:16,040
Get me out of here!

1133
02:04:17,600 --> 02:04:19,560
You won't get away with this!

1134
02:04:27,960 --> 02:04:29,240
Let me go!

1135
02:05:41,200 --> 02:05:43,120
There are a few abandoned
places around here.

1136
02:05:43,600 --> 02:05:45,360
Therefore, we'll spread out and search.

1137
02:05:50,720 --> 02:05:53,920
Stay alert and stay in touch.

1138
02:05:54,880 --> 02:05:57,040
You two, check this side.
You check the other side.

1139
02:06:13,680 --> 02:06:15,360
I'm checking here. You keep going.

1140
02:06:24,560 --> 02:06:26,640
Why are you doing this to me?

1141
02:06:26,920 --> 02:06:28,800
Let me go.

1142
02:06:29,280 --> 02:06:31,120
Is anyone there?

1143
02:06:32,080 --> 02:06:33,640
I told you to let me go.

1144
02:06:34,880 --> 02:06:36,440
Help me!

1145
02:06:37,040 --> 02:06:38,560
Can't anyone hear me?!

1146
02:07:29,720 --> 02:07:32,080
Where have you been, Mercan? Where?

1147
02:08:31,200 --> 02:08:32,760
What's this tanker doing here?

1148
02:08:40,280 --> 02:08:42,360
Cemal. I think I found her.

1149
02:09:01,880 --> 02:09:03,720
Help!

1150
02:09:10,200 --> 02:09:12,040
Why are you doing this?!

1151
02:09:16,760 --> 02:09:18,320
Please, set me free.

1152
02:09:19,360 --> 02:09:21,160
Let me go!

1153
02:09:23,400 --> 02:09:25,360
Help me!

1154
02:09:42,400 --> 02:09:43,800
You deserved to die like this.

1155
02:09:44,320 --> 02:09:46,240
Finally, I'm getting rid of you.

1156
02:09:54,800 --> 02:09:56,280
Help!

1157
02:09:57,640 --> 02:09:59,000
Help me!

1158
02:09:59,760 --> 02:10:02,440
Mercan! I'm here, Mercan!

1159
02:10:03,400 --> 02:10:05,040
Mercan!

1160
02:10:11,240 --> 02:10:13,480
-Someone’s here. -Who?

1161
02:10:13,640 --> 02:10:15,840
I don’t know, but I hear someone’s outside.

1162
02:10:16,200 --> 02:10:19,000
It might be Ateş. Don’t touch him.

1163
02:10:19,600 --> 02:10:21,600
But don’t let him save her either.

1164
02:10:22,360 --> 02:10:24,960
That girl is not leaving that place alive.

1165
02:11:53,680 --> 02:11:55,720
Mercan!

1166
02:12:57,240 --> 02:12:59,720
-Mercan. -Ateş.

1167
02:13:03,480 --> 02:13:06,120
Look, I’m here now. Don’t be scared.

1168
02:13:08,160 --> 02:13:10,760
I knew it… I knew you'd come.

1169
02:13:12,280 --> 02:13:15,400
I won’t let anything
happen to you. I promise.

1170
02:13:15,880 --> 02:13:18,000
I’m never letting you
out of my sight again.

1171
02:13:31,360 --> 02:13:33,600
Ateş…

1172
02:13:40,560 --> 02:13:42,280
Ateş!

1173
02:13:49,080 --> 02:13:50,680
Ateş.

1174
02:14:03,360 --> 02:14:05,080
Ateş.

1175
02:14:12,680 --> 02:14:14,400
Ateş.

1176
02:14:20,000 --> 02:14:21,840
Ateş.

1177
02:14:23,080 --> 02:14:25,680
Mercan. Don't be scared. I'm right here.

1178
02:14:26,160 --> 02:14:28,120
Hold on. I’ll save you. I promise.

1179
02:14:33,920 --> 02:14:35,640
Do whatever you want to me!

1180
02:14:35,720 --> 02:14:36,960
Let her go.

1181
02:14:37,080 --> 02:14:39,400
Let go of her. Let her go.

1182
02:14:39,480 --> 02:14:40,760
Mercan, hold on.

1183
02:14:40,840 --> 02:14:42,880
Hold on!

1184
02:14:51,280 --> 02:14:53,000
Let her go.

1185
02:15:07,160 --> 02:15:09,520
No, Mercan! Mercan!

1186
02:15:10,160 --> 02:15:13,120
Mercaaaaaan!

1187
02:15:36,000 --> 02:15:37,760
You won't get away this time.

1188
02:15:39,240 --> 02:15:42,600
I'll never let anything happen to her.

1189
02:17:49,920 --> 02:17:52,800
Mercan… stay with me, please!

1190
02:17:53,720 --> 02:17:55,320
Hold on Mercan. Open your eyes.

1191
02:17:56,080 --> 02:17:58,080
Mercan, I’m begging you. Hold on.

1192
02:17:59,440 --> 02:18:00,800
Mercan.

1193
02:18:00,880 --> 02:18:03,080
You’re not leaving me
like this. Do you hear me?

1194
02:18:03,280 --> 02:18:04,800
I won’t let you.

1195
02:18:05,000 --> 02:18:06,520
Come on, open your eyes.

1196
02:18:06,960 --> 02:18:08,560
Turn your back.

1197
02:18:12,840 --> 02:18:14,240
Mercan?

1198
02:18:14,360 --> 02:18:16,520
See? You're better now.

1199
02:18:18,560 --> 02:18:21,720
You're fine. Nothing will
happen to you. Nothing.

1200
02:18:22,200 --> 02:18:24,040
You hear me? Nothing will happen to you!

1201
02:18:24,800 --> 02:18:28,520
Come on my darling. Open
your eyes. Come on, breathe.

1202
02:18:30,640 --> 02:18:32,160
Say something my beautiful girl.

1203
02:18:32,440 --> 02:18:34,440
Come on. Come on, my pearl Mercan.

1204
02:18:35,040 --> 02:18:36,240
Come on open your eyes.

1205
02:18:42,760 --> 02:18:45,440
Come on open your eyes, Mercan!

1206
02:18:45,840 --> 02:18:47,520
Open your eyes!

1207
02:18:52,920 --> 02:18:54,480
ANLAMADIM

1208
02:18:54,600 --> 02:18:56,520
Mercan?

1209
02:18:58,640 --> 02:19:00,520
Come on.

1210
02:19:04,520 --> 02:19:06,640
Don’t leave me. You hear me?

1211
02:19:07,120 --> 02:19:08,760
Don’t go. Don’t leave me.

1212
02:19:09,040 --> 02:19:12,000
Open your eyes, Mercan! I’m begging you.

1213
02:19:20,600 --> 02:19:22,520
You can't go anywhere. You hear me?

1214
02:19:22,680 --> 02:19:26,480
You can't go anywhere! Nowhere, Mercan!

1215
02:19:26,920 --> 02:19:29,200
Mercan, open your eyes!

1216
02:19:34,400 --> 02:19:36,560
Mercan. Mercan.

1217
02:19:37,080 --> 02:19:38,760
I'm asking you to breathe, Mercan!

1218
02:19:39,120 --> 02:19:40,600
Mercan, breathe!

1219
02:19:40,680 --> 02:19:42,360
You can't go anywhere. You hear me?

1220
02:19:42,560 --> 02:19:44,640
You can't go anywhere. I won't let you.

1221
02:19:44,720 --> 02:19:46,480
You hear me? Come on, Mercan!

1222
02:19:46,800 --> 02:19:50,520
No, no, no. Open your eyes, Mercan!

1223
02:19:51,640 --> 02:19:53,200
Mercan!

1224
02:19:53,280 --> 02:19:56,440
Mercaaaaaan!
